commits.commitMessage:
QTIX5510-3331 - Add reverse lookup script - rev_ST.sh

Description:
Allows fetching relevant info associated with md5sums
md5sums are typically reported by AT!STEFS command on the UE.
at!stefs?
rtsar_config_fcc        53dc5d43033c1140d49bf0b984ab8b8bc56a92ce29c444295256d95f1f9e320b
rtsar_config_row        92158f7647e638d3add3341dd24bc2e7adf90fb89ce4a04e7d3ab50e59e802cb

Either of the two md5sums could be used as lookup parameter for rev_ST.sh
The output helps identify following info:
ommit hash
OEMID
ChangeID
which can be further used to fetch the corresponding excel / csv files.

Resolves:
QTIX5510-3331

Change-Id: Icc70d9e39b7da12fc5412eb0e5b88abfd265938b
commits.subject: QTIX5510-3331 - Add reverse lookup script - rev_ST.sh

commits.commitMessage:
Add conversion tool from xlsx to csv

Description:
Add python script capable to convert
multi-worksheets excel documents into a single csv file
It relies on openpyxl library
Sort on filename/worksheet to ensure predictable concatenation order
Force pandas to use openpyxl as Excel read engine

Resolves: QTIX5510-3041
Change-Id: I978d543a8ccd6548a4b3214565bb3fdb4718ec98
commits.subject: Add conversion tool from xlsx to csv

comments.message:
glob.glob relies on os.listdir.
os.listdir(path) Return a list containing the names of the entries in the directory given by path. The list is in arbitrary order.
In order to produce consistent results, sorting needs to be applied.

Testing shows now the output files are identical between Ubuntu 16.04 and 18.04, while previously they had different order of the sections.

Python pandas are working with xlrd as default engine.
However, latest version of xlrd library does not support xlsx file format.
That forces us to use openpyxl library instead.
I made corresponding changes to avoid referencing xlrd altogether.

Confirmed this implementation is consistent across different versions of Ubuntu.
I am fine with this final implementation. Will merge it shortly (after updating parent commit with csv files generated by this script version).
